{"ts": "2026-06-07T00:55:12.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L2 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l2", "tokens_in": 229, "tokens_out": 539, "elapsed_ms": 5416, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\nRules:\n- Each subtask should be a focused, self-contained unit of work\n- Include file names and output expectations in descriptions\n- For simple tasks, 2-3 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- FRONTEND: Always include an index.html (main entry page). Additional pages\n  (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine, but index.html must exist and link to them.\n  Subtask descriptions should specify what content/sections each file contains.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nCreate an ecommerce landing page for Summit Roast, a premium specialty coffee brand sourced from high-altitude farms. Include lifestyle imagery, product benefits, subscription options, customer reviews, and a shop section. Use warm earth tones and premium typography.", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T00:58:04.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L2 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l2", "tokens_in": 1446, "tokens_out": 1892, "elapsed_ms": 171427, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Agent Creator (Level 2 — Template-Based). Your role: create worker agent configurations by selecting from predefined templates.\n\n## Available Templates for this Specialty\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"role\": \"ux_designer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a UX/UI Content Designer. Generate real content, copy, and image prompts for the web page. Save as content_brief.json.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": []\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"role\": \"html_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are an HTML Developer. Write semantic HTML5. Save as index.html. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"role\": \"css_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a CSS Developer. Write modern CSS with variables, flexbox, grid. Save as styles.css. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/css_styling.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"role\": \"js_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a JavaScript Developer. Write vanilla ES6+ JS. Save as app.js. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"role\": \"frontend_tester\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a Frontend Tester. Validate HTML, CSS, JS files. Write test_report.json with structured issues.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"tester/e2e_testing.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"setup-project\",\n      \"description\": \"Create project directory structure with css/, js/, and images/ folders. Initialize index.html as the main entry page with proper HTML5 structure, including links to stylesheet and favicon. Set up main.css with warm earth tone color variables (e.g., #5C4033, #D2B48C, #F5F5DC) and import premium typography (e.g., 'Playfair Display' and 'Lato' from Google Fonts).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"design-hero\",\n      \"description\": \"Build the hero section in index.html featuring a full-width lifestyle image of coffee in mountainous terrain, overlay text with brand name 'Summit Roast', tagline, and a call-to-action button. Style with CSS to use warm earth tones, elegant typography, and responsive layout. Ensure the section conveys premium quality and origin story.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"product-benefits\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a section in index.html highlighting product benefits: 'High-Altitude Sourcing', 'Small-Batch Roasting', and 'Sustainable Farms'. Include icons or small images, descriptive text, and styled cards. Ensure visual hierarchy using premium typography and spacing consistent with brand tone.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"subscription-options\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement a subscription section in index.html with 3 pricing tiers (e.g., 'Monthly', 'Bi-Monthly', 'Quarterly'). Each tier should include price, coffee type, delivery frequency, and a 'Subscribe' button. Style with clean cards, subtle borders, and earth-tone accents. Include a note about flexibility and free shipping.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"customer-reviews\",\n      \"description\": \"Create a customer testimonials section in index.html with 3-4 review cards. Each card should include a customer photo (placeholder), name, rating stars, and a short quote about coffee quality or experience. Style with rounded images, soft backgrounds, and responsive grid layout.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"shop-section\",\n      \"description\": \"Build a shop section in index.html displaying 4-6 featured coffee products. Each product card should include image, name, origin, price, and 'Add to Cart' button. Link to a future shop page if needed. Ensure consistent styling with earth tones, elegant fonts, and hover effects. Include a 'View All Products' CTA below the grid.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n- FRONTEND FILE NAMES: The html worker always outputs index.html (the main page).\n  The css worker always outputs styles.css. The js worker always outputs app.js.\n  Additional HTML pages (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine but index.html\n  is the canonical main entry. Add section-specific instructions to the prompt,\n  do NOT rename the output file.\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
