{"ts": "2026-06-07T01:01:58.000Z", "event": "report", "msg": "L2 report assembly", "agent": "report-l2", "tokens_in": 990, "tokens_out": 750, "elapsed_ms": 12125, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Report agent. Merge all worker results into a clean Markdown report.\n\n## Worker Results\n### html\nI've completed the project setup with the following structure:\n\n1. Created `css/main.css` with:\n   - Google Fonts import for Playfair Display and Lato\n   - CSS custom properties for warm earth tone color palette\n   - Base typography and color styles\n\n2. Created `index.html` with:\n   - Proper HTML5 structure\n   - Viewport meta tag\n   - Link to CSS stylesheet\n   - Placeholder for favicon\n   - Basic semantic structure with header, main, and footer\n\n3. Created `js/app.js` with a basic initialization script\n\n4. Added a placeholder `images/favicon.png`\n\nThe color palette uses warm earth tones:\n- Dark Brown: #5C4033\n- Tan: #D2B48C\n- Cream Background: #F5F5DC\n- Additional Coffee Brown: #6F4E37\n- Light Khaki Accent: #F0E68C\n\nTypography is set with Playfair Display for headings and Lato for body text, imported from Google Fonts.\n\nWould you like me to validate the HTML or make any further modifications?\n\n### css\nI've created the hero section for Summit Roast Coffee with a focus on premium quality and origin story. Let me break down the key design decisions:\n\n### CSS Design Highlights\n1. **Color Palette**: \n   - Used warm earth tones reflecting coffee and mountain landscapes\n   - Dark Brown (#5C4033) for depth\n   - Tan (#D2B48C) for elegant highlights\n   - Cream Background (#F5F5DC) for softness\n   - Coffee Brown (#6F4E37) for CTA button\n   - Khaki Accent (#F0E68C) for hover states\n\n2. **Typography**:\n   - Playfair Display for headings: Elegant, serif font suggesting premium quality\n   - Lato for body text: Clean, modern sans-serif for readability\n   - Fluid typography using `clamp()` for responsive sizing\n   - Generous letter-spacing and thoughtful font weights\n\n3. **Hero Section Layout**:\n   - Full-width background image with gradient overlay\n   - Centered content with semi-transparent background\n   - Responsive design that adapts to different screen sizes\n   - Hover effects on CTA button for interactivity\n\n4. **Accessibility Considerations**:\n   - Reduced motion media query\n   - High color contrast\n   - Responsive typography\n   - Semantic HTML structure\n\n### Next Steps\n1. Add a mountain coffee scene image to `images/hero-coffee-mountains.jpg`\n2. Implement navigation in the header\n3. Add content to the footer\n4. Consider adding more sections showcasing coffee origin and products\n\nWould you like me to proceed with any of these next steps or make any adjustments to the current design?\n\n### tester\nI've added a new \"Product Benefits\" section to the `index.html` file with the following key features:\n\n1. **Semantic HTML Structure**\n   - Used `<section>` with a descriptive class\n   - Included a container for responsive layout\n   - Added semantic headings (`<h2>`, `<h3>`)\n\n2. **Inline SVG Icons**\n   - Created custom mountain-themed icons for each benefit\n   - Used stroke-based design to match the brand's aesthetic\n   - Implemented hover and interaction states in CSS\n\n3. **Responsive Grid Layout**\n   - Used CSS Grid with `auto-fit` and `minmax()` for flexible card arrangement\n   - Mobile-first approach with single-column layout\n   - Responsive breakpoints for tablet and desktop views\n\n4. **Visual Design**\n   - Consistent color palette using existing earth tones\n   - Hover effects with subtle elevation and shadow\n   - Circular icon backgrounds with brand colors\n   - Typography maintains the premium, mountain-inspired feel\n\n5. **Accessibility Considerations**\n   - High color contrast\n   - Semantic HTML structure\n   - Reduced motion support\n   - Readable typography\n\nI validated both the HTML and CSS, and they passed all checks. The section is now ready for integration and further refinement.\n\nWould you like me to make any additional modifications or add more details to the product benefits section?\n\n## Files Created\n- css/main.css: /* Summit Roast Coffee - Main Stylesheet */\n- images/favicon.png: Placeholder for favicon image\n- index.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- js/app.js: // Summit Roast Coffee - Main JavaScript File\n\n## Guidelines\n- Group results by worker\n- Include summary table with worker name, status, and one-liner\n- Reference file paths\n- Keep the report concise\n\nOutput the full Markdown report.", "meta": {}}
